div.div:
Pmod CLS
custom driver
interface.
Three commands can be
issued: clear display,
write text line 1,
write text line 2.
128-bit ASCII data
input per LCD text
line.

div.div:
The Pmod CLS custom driver operates by waiting for the ATmega48 microcontroller to boot. It then indicates when a
command is ready by outputting '1' on the Command Ready port.
A pulse on Command Write Clear Display instructs the driver to transmit via SPI an ASCII text escape sequence to
the ATmega48. The ASCII text escape sequence is a hard-coded text value that instructs that the LCD display be
cleared of text on its two lines.
A pulse on Command Write Text Line 1 instructs an FSM to load the Data ASCII Line 1 input and then issue a
sequence of sending two ASCII text pieces to the microcontroller. The first text piece instructs that the Pmod CLS be
controlled to position its text writing cursor at the start of the LCD's first text line. The second text piece is the
16 character data value that is to be written to line 1 of the LCD.
A pulse on Command Write Text Line 2 instructs an FSM to load the Data ASCII Line 2 input and then issue a
sequence of sending two ASCII text pieces to the microcontroller. The first text piece instructs that the Pmod CLS be
controlled to position its text writing cursor at the start of the LCD's second text line. The second text piece is the
16 character data value that is to be written to line 2 of the LCD.
Other than the Command Write Clear Display which clears the display; there is no soft reset function to reboot
the microcontroller and/or reset the display..
